modules.description: This module enables creating and customizing interactive pie charts via D3.js by providing typed configuration options for visual properties, data handling, and user interactions. It operates on structured settings objects that define chart dimensions, hierarchical data with grouping rules, label formatting, tooltip behavior, and event handlers for interactions like clicks or hover effects. Typical use cases include visualizing categorical data distributions with dynamic color schemes, segmented tooltips, and responsive visual feedback in web applications.

This module provides typed configuration and rendering functions for creating interactive pie charts with D3.js. It works with structured data including categorical values, hierarchical groupings, and visual settings like colors, labels, and tooltips. Concrete use cases include displaying dynamic data distributions with customizable layouts, interactive legends, and responsive user feedback in web-based dashboards.
